{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_timeout_event", "label": "timeout_event", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L31", "doc": "Watchdog countdown event: fires when the counter reaches zero. On the first timeout it latches the interrupt and reloads the counter; on a second timeout (interrupt still pending) it asserts the reset signal when RESEN is enabled, then keeps reloading and counting."}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_simple_cycle_event", "label": "simple_cycle_event", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L31"}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_timeout_event_event", "label": "event()", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L32", "signature": "method event()"}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_is_device_locked", "label": "is_device_locked()", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L61", "signature": "method is_device_locked() -> (bool)", "doc": "Returns true while the device is locked. When locked, all register writes are ignored; the lock is cleared only by writing the magic unlock value 0x1ACCE551 to WDOGLOCK."}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_counter_value", "label": "counter_value", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L68", "signature": "attribute counter_value is (uint64_attr)", "doc": "Backing store for the watchdog down-counter. Holds the count and models it lazily: the live value is derived from elapsed cycles and the clock divider only when read, instead of being decremented every cycle."}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_uint64_attr", "label": "uint64_attr", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L68", "signature": "attribute counter_value is (uint64_attr)"}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_counter_value_reset", "label": "reset()", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L71", "signature": "method reset()", "doc": "Resets the counter to its power-on value (0xFFFFFFFF)."}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_counter_value_curr_value", "label": "curr_value()", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L78", "signature": "method curr_value() -> (uint32)", "doc": "Lazily computes the current count from the cycles elapsed since the last update, scaled by the clock divider. Returns 0 once the counter has underflowed, and the stored value while the timer is not running."}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_counter_value_refresh", "label": "refresh()", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L96", "signature": "method refresh()", "doc": "Folds the lazily-computed live value back into the stored counter."}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_counter_value_set_value", "label": "set_value()", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L101", "signature": "method set_value(uint64 new_val)", "doc": "Stores a new counter value (used on reload and when freezing the counter)."}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_counter_value_get_value", "label": "get_value()", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L106", "signature": "method get_value() -> (uint64)", "doc": "Returns the stored counter value without recomputing elapsed time."}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_get_divider", "label": "get_divider()", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L114", "signature": "method get_divider() -> (uint64)", "doc": "Maps the WDOGCONTROL.STEP_VALUE field to the clock divider (1/2/4/8/16), defaulting to 1 for reserved encodings. The divider sets how many input clock cycles correspond to one decrement of the watchdog counter."}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_schedule_timeout", "label": "schedule_timeout()", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L127", "signature": "method schedule_timeout()", "doc": "(Re)posts the countdown event. Cancels any pending event, then, when the timer is enabled (INTEN set and clock running), schedules the event for the number of cycles until the counter reaches zero (remaining count * divider)."}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_update_interrupt_signal", "label": "update_interrupt_signal()", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L143", "signature": "method update_interrupt_signal()", "doc": "Drives the WDOGINT output to match interrupt state: asserts when an interrupt is pending and INTEN is set, deasserts otherwise. Skipped in integration test mode, where WDOGITOP drives the signal directly."}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_update_reset_signal", "label": "update_reset_signal()", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L165", "signature": "method update_reset_signal()", "doc": "Drives the WDOGRES output to match reset state: asserts when a reset is pending, deasserts otherwise. Skipped in integration test mode, where WDOGITOP drives the signal directly."}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_watchdogregisters", "label": "WatchdogRegisters", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L185", "doc": "Register bank holding the device's runtime side-effects. The bank layout and reset values come from the WatchdogRegisters_temp template in wdt-registers.dml; this declaration adds the read/write behavior."}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_watchdogregisters_temp", "label": "WatchdogRegisters_temp", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L185"}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_watchdogregisters_wdogload", "label": "WDOGLOAD", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L189", "doc": "Load register: the value reloaded into the counter on each timeout and on interrupt clear. Writes are ignored while locked and do not reload the counter immediately unless INTEN transitions 0->1."}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_watchdogregisters_wdogload_write_register", "label": "write_register()", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L190", "signature": "method write_register(uint64 val, uint64 enabled_bytes, void *aux)"}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_watchdogregisters_wdogload_read_register", "label": "read_register()", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L203", "signature": "method read_register(uint64 enabled_bytes, void *aux) -> (uint64)"}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_watchdogregisters_wdogvalue", "label": "WDOGVALUE", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L210", "doc": "Value register (read-only): returns the live counter value via lazy evaluation rather than a continuously decremented field."}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_watchdogregisters_wdogvalue_read_register", "label": "read_register()", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L211", "signature": "method read_register(uint64 enabled_bytes, void *aux) -> (uint64)"}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_watchdogregisters_wdogcontrol", "label": "WDOGCONTROL", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L219", "doc": "Control register: INTEN enables the watchdog and RESEN enables reset on a second timeout. Toggling INTEN reloads or freezes the counter and (re)schedules the countdown; STEP_VALUE selects the clock divider."}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_watchdogregisters_wdogcontrol_write_register", "label": "write_register()", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L220", "signature": "method write_register(uint64 val, uint64 enabled_bytes, void *aux)"}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_watchdogregisters_wdogcontrol_read_register", "label": "read_register()", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L267", "signature": "method read_register(uint64 enabled_bytes, void *aux) -> (uint64)"}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_watchdogregisters_wdogintclr", "label": "WDOGINTCLR", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L274", "doc": "Interrupt clear register: any write clears the pending interrupt, lowers WDOGINT, reloads the counter from WDOGLOAD and reschedules the countdown."}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_watchdogregisters_wdogintclr_write_register", "label": "write_register()", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L275", "signature": "method write_register(uint64 val, uint64 enabled_bytes, void *aux)"}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_watchdogregisters_wdogris", "label": "WDOGRIS", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L298", "doc": "Raw interrupt status register: bit 0 reflects the pending interrupt before masking by INTEN."}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_watchdogregisters_wdogris_read_register", "label": "read_register()", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L299", "signature": "method read_register(uint64 enabled_bytes, void *aux) -> (uint64)"}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_watchdogregisters_wdogmis", "label": "WDOGMIS", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L306", "doc": "Masked interrupt status register: bit 0 is the raw status ANDed with INTEN, i.e. the interrupt as seen by the interrupt controller."}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_watchdogregisters_wdogmis_read_register", "label": "read_register()", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L307", "signature": "method read_register(uint64 enabled_bytes, void *aux) -> (uint64)"}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_watchdogregisters_wdoglock", "label": "WDOGLOCK", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L315", "doc": "Lock register: writing the magic value 0x1ACCE551 unlocks the device; any other write locks it. Reads return 1 when locked, 0 when unlocked."}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_watchdogregisters_wdoglock_write_register", "label": "write_register()", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L316", "signature": "method write_register(uint64 val, uint64 enabled_bytes, void *aux)"}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_watchdogregisters_wdoglock_read_register", "label": "read_register()", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L325", "signature": "method read_register(uint64 enabled_bytes, void *aux) -> (uint64)"}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_watchdogregisters_wdogitcr", "label": "WDOGITCR", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L333", "doc": "Integration test control register: enables integration test mode, in which the output signals are driven directly via WDOGITOP. Leaving test mode restores the normal interrupt and reset signal states."}
{"id": "wdt_dml_wdt_watchdogregisters_wdogitcr_write_register", "label": "write_register()", "source_file": "wdt_dml/wdt.dml", "source_location": "L334", "signature": "method write_register(uint64 val, uint64 enabled_bytes, void *aux)"}
